                "invention-title": [
                    "Reverse electrodialysis metal smelting low-grade heat energy hydrogen production method and device",
                    "一种逆电渗析法金属冶炼低品位热能制氢方法及装置"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention provides a method and a device for producing hydrogen by using low-grade heat energy in metal smelting through a reverse electrodialysis method, and belongs to the technical field of energy conservation and environmental protection. According to the hydrogen production method, on the basis of the reverse electrodialysis principle and the low-temperature solution concentration regeneration principle, low-grade heat energy generated in the metal smelting process serves as driving force, according to respective cycle work of cooling liquid, a working medium solution and electrode liquid, heat energy is continuously converted into chemical potential energy, then the chemical potential energy is converted into hydrogen energy, and continuous hydrogen production is achieved. Hydrogen and byproduct oxygen generated in the hydrogen production process serve as a reducing agent (or fuel) and an oxidizing agent respectively and are coupled to the high-temperature section of the smelting process to participate in the reaction. The conversion process of heat energy, chemical potential energy, hydrogen and oxygen and coupling into the smelting process is achieved. The low-grade heat energy in the metal smelting process can be effectively converted and utilized; energy recycling is realized; and modularization is easy to realize."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明提供一种逆电渗析法金属冶炼低品位热能制氢方法及装置，属于节能环保技术领域。该制氢方法以逆电渗析原理和低温溶液浓度再生原理为基础，以金属冶炼过程中产生的低品位热能为驱动力，根据冷却液、工质溶液及电极液的各自循环工作，持续地将热能转换为化学势能，并进而再转换为氢能，实现连续制氢。制氢过程中产生的氢气及副产物氧气分别作为还原剂(或燃料)和氧化剂耦合到冶炼过程的高温段参与反应。即实现“热能→化学势能→氢气氧气→耦合进冶炼流程”的转化过程。本发明能够使金属冶炼过程中的低品位热能有效转换利用；实现能源循环利用；易于实现模块化。"
                }
            ]
